peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "Residence Manager at The Ascott Limited", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Chin", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C5603AQEkiLr8R-_b1g/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1625142536426?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=7eDk_OBYtKtFogKBeIDUGHYP7eXVRwJbLlE8If4jpZc", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "nixon-chin-b34b8352", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAs1RpgBALOKs8IvQGY-5FEqhcwUUF7vaBc", "profilePic": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D03AQFnHEtKaZHfWQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1656158507053?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=MIamBlBgMdv_A4MDM5GGqKAQG54rbD1wLgn15RzXF6M", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D03AQFnHEtKaZHfWQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1656158507053?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=MIamBlBgMdv_A4MDM5GGqKAQG54rbD1wLgn15RzXF6M", "publicIdentifier": "nigeldouwes", "recommendations/0/context": "Nigel was Anna's client", "recommendations/0/date": "November 12, 2023", "recommendations/0/description": "In my encounters with Anna, she has always proven to be a dynamic problem solver with the capability to put herself in the clients shoes. \n\nWithin the 1.5 years working together, Anna helped to increase our mutual business exponentially by providing real-time solutions that have always been a win-win for both parties. \n\nHer optimistic personality and drive made her a very engaging partner to work with and gives me the confidence she will succeed in any future ventures related to her expertise. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Anna Fhaumnuaypol", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Digital PR Manager, Global at Minor Hotels | Former Pre-Opening Marketing & Comms Lead at Marriott | Previously in Account Management at Expedia", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/annasfha/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACK_UXAByxcSmVUQ6xyiJmaYQErQDMHDyD8", "recommendations/1/context": "Nigel worked with Fretty Carolina Aulia but on different teams", "recommendations/1/date": "March 10, 2023", "recommendations/1/description": "I had the pleasure to work with Fretty during her tenure as Brand Manager for Préférence Hotels. She excelled in her job by delivering strong, yet creative brand guidelines providing an unified guest journey across different hotels, while keeping the individual characteristics of each property in tact. \n\nFretty is always determined, yet easy to work with and open to new ideas. Using her inter-personal skills she was able to get all layers of the organization on board to follow through on new guidelines and standards. She gives people ownership of their ideas and input, ensuring a strong brand culture. \n\nI feel Fretty would be an asset to any company looking to enhance, revamp or establish a strong brand culture. ", "recommendations/1/name": "Fretty Carolina Aulia Hutapea", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Hotel Branding Architect/Designer | Assisting Hotel Owners and Hotel Operators | Developing Hotel Brand Concept and Assisting its Implementation through Architecture/ID | Hotel Copywriting", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/frettyaulia/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAArfPeMBSl00FA5FExq1A1y6Ygx0VfeM9I4", "recommendations/2/context": "Nigel managed Tian directly", "recommendations/2/date": "November 19, 2020", "recommendations/2/description": "I have had the pleasure to work with Nova during his tenure at The Tamarind Resort in Nusa Lembongan, where he grew into a valued asset in the finance team, before taking the lead in this department. Nova is hard working, loyal with a tremendous understand of his job and the technicalities in finance. He never stops learning and has shown this by completing an addition eduction outside of his work obligations. It has been a true pleasure working with him and genuinely hope our paths will cross in the future. \n\nTo Nova, keep it up! ", "recommendations/2/name": "Tian Nova", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Finance & Accounting", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/tian-nova-81145a67/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA4gfQ0BUIWwzSo_BUF1PFyOwBX6seaZESw", "recommendations/3/context": "Nigel worked with Puspa on the same team", "recommendations/3/date": "October 21, 2015", "recommendations/3/description": "I had the pleasure of working with Puspa during her time at Plataran Hotels & Resorts in her role as Corporate Director of Sales & Marketing. We worked closely together as she guided me in setting and achieving sales budgets, exploring sales & marketing strategies and conducting sales visits. \n\nPuspa is one of the most charismatic and determined colleagues I had the pleasure of working with. Her leadership and organization set her off to determine and achieve both personal as company goals in timely manners.\n\nPuspa will be a true asset to any company looking to develop a strong sales team based on creative visioning and strong leadership. I wish Puspa all the best in his future career.", "recommendations/3/name": "Puspa Rianti", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "General Manager | Luxury Hospitality Strategist | Driving Commercial Growth | Brand Positioning & Guest Experience Excellence", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/puspa-rianti-07b1b245/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAl2JN8BVmfFkd6Wcro31yB3Nv0KvmI0GBI", "recommendations/4/context": "Nigel worked with Sidney on the same team", "recommendations/4/date": "August 24, 2015", "recommendations/4/description": "I had the pleasure to work with Sidney during his period as Operations Manager at Atlantis Beachclub in Labuan Bajo, Flores. As a peer I have witnessed Sidney rapidly develop a strong and motivated team with attention to the fullest details of 5 star hospitality service. As a natural leader Sidney has been able to transmit his skills and vision to the team by focusing on training and talent development. \n\nSidney is a pleasant presence on the floor making time for his guests and developing the company’s standards by assessing guest satisfaction. He is a determined worker and besides a great person to work with. \n\nSidney will be a true asset to any company looking to develop a strong team or adept fresh, innovative concepts in the hospitality sector. I wish Sidney all the best in his future career. ", "recommendations/4/name": "Sidney Visser", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Head of Sales & Event Rentals at Desert River", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vissersidney/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABkyo2gBmRZDiIiRwDl0wclhJe5sdp608rE", "recommendationsReceived/0/context": "Nigel was Anna's client", "recommendationsReceived/0/date": "November 12, 2023", "recommendationsReceived/0/description": "Nigel was one of my hotel partners during my time at Expedia Group, where he assumed the role of General Manager for Somerset Rama 9. \n\nNigel's hands-on approach, extensive knowledge, and fearless willingness to embrace new strategies and ways of doing things were invaluable, especially in the evolving landscape of post-COVID hospitality. His growth-oriented mindset facilitated seamless communication and collaboration. This led to tangible outcomes for the hotel's performance on the platform and an overall increase in revenue within a matter of months of our initiatives.\n\nI am highly confident that his impactful leadership qualities will shine in any property he chooses to take on.", "recommendationsReceived/0/name": "Anna Fhaumnuaypol", "recommendationsReceived/0/subtitle": "Digital PR Manager, Global at Minor Hotels | Former Pre-Opening Marketing & Comms Lead at Marriott | Previously in Account Management at Expedia", "recommendationsReceived/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/annasfha/", "recommendationsReceived/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACK_UXAByxcSmVUQ6xyiJmaYQErQDMHDyD8", "recommendationsReceived/1/context": "Fretty Carolina Aulia worked with Nigel but on different teams", "recommendationsReceived/1/date": "March 10, 2023", "recommendationsReceived/1/description": "I have the pleasure of 5 years experience working with Nigel at TAUZIA International Management. He is one of the memorable people I get to work with.\n\nWhen I first met him, he was on board as the GM for The Tamarind Nusa Lembongan, one of the Préférence Hotels. And with his hard work, he had made his ladder up to be the Cluster General Manager for Préférence Hotels. \n\nHe has made it easier for me as brand manager to develop Préférence Hotels. He was very critical on the brand development, and continued opening the box by raising important operational issues, yet was also offering options and solutions. He is also very considerate, he understood that some development may work and some may not. He never lost his faith in my works and for that I am thankful. \n\nI sincerely hope for every success for him! Hoping someday we can cross path again in the future!", "recommendationsReceived/1/name": "Fretty Carolina Aulia Hutapea", "recommendationsReceived/1/subtitle": "Hotel Branding Architect/Designer | Assisting Hotel Owners and Hotel Operators | Developing Hotel Brand Concept and Assisting its Implementation through Architecture/ID | Hotel Copywriting", "recommendationsReceived/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/frettyaulia/", "recommendationsReceived/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAArfPeMBSl00FA5FExq1A1y6Ygx0VfeM9I4", "recommendationsReceived/2/context": "Sidney worked with Nigel on the same team", "recommendationsReceived/2/date": "August 24, 2015", "recommendationsReceived/2/description": "During my time working for Plataran Hotels & Resorts in Labuan Bajo (Indonesia), I had the pleasure to work closely together with Nigel on a daily base. He was leading the Plataran Komodo Resort while I was leading the Atlantis Beachclub by Plataran.\n\nNigel is hands-on, always reachable and immediately responds to challenges. Being a strong leader and revenue focused, he managed to improve the revenue of Plataran Komodo Resort and bring the service and efficiency of all departments to a higher level.\n\nHe possesses the interpersonal skill of building positive and strong relationships with all stakeholders, and mastered to transform this skill into value for the company. His priority are his guests and he is often praised in TripAdvisor reviews for his commitment and leading his team to go that extra mile.\n\nI have no hesitation in recommending Nigel to any upscale hospitality company, which will surely profit from his hands-on leadership style and commitment. ", "recommendationsReceived/2/name": "Sidney Visser", "recommendationsReceived/2/subtitle": "Head of Sales & Event Rentals at Desert River", "recommendationsReceived/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/vissersidney/", "recommendationsReceived/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABkyo2gBmRZDiIiRwDl0wclhJe5sdp608rE", "skills/0/title": "Empowerment", "skills/1/title": "Guest Satisfaction", "skills/2/title": "Coaching & Mentoring", "skills/3/title": "Driving Results", "skills/4/title": "Event Management", "skills/5/title": "Event Planning", "skills/6/title": "Customer Service", "skills/7/title": "HACCP", "skills/8/title": "Hospitality", "skills/9/title": "Marketing", "skills/10/title": "Social Media", "skills/11/title": "Gastronomy", "skills/12/title": "Hospitality Management", "skills/13/title": "Food & Beverage", "skills/14/title": "Cost Control", "skills/15/title": "Concept Development", "skills/16/title": "Concept Implementation", "skills/17/title": "Menu Engineering", "skills/18/title": "Facebook", "skills/19/title": "Hotel Management", "totalExperienceYears": "18.2", "totalRecommendationsGiven": "5", "totalRecommendationsReceived": "3", "urn": "ACoAAAaNoJgBqpvhdl7bHgsd_c_YhWtsAD4b2mQ", "volunteerAndAwards/0/description": "Stichting Vrienden van Stef has been founded in loving memory of our friend Stef, who lost his live in the unfair battle against Ewing Sarcoma cancer. The foundation organizes a wide range of events in order to collect funds. These events, according Stef's lifestyle, including sporting events, fundraisers, festivities are helping the foundation to support those who are giving battle against cancer at the moment. \nBeside supporting the research focusing on the Ewing Sarcoma (a difficult treatable form of bone-cancer that mostly exists among young children), the foundation tries to mentally support those kids that are fighting there fight by organizing fun fairs in hospitals.\n\nwww.stichtingvriendenvanstef.nl", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/months": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/duration/years": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/month": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/end_date/year": "0", "volunteerAndAwards/0/industry": "Health", "volunteerAndAwards/0/is_current_position": "true", "volunteerAndAwards/0/organization": "Stichting Vrienden van Stef", "volunteerAndAwards/0/role": "Co-Founder & Board Member", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/month": "8", "volunteerAndAwards/0/start_date/year": "2012"}$$::jsonb),
