eant I had\nthe ability to work at virtually all positions and they also gave me opportunity to gain deeper\ninsight into the company. I worked as a front desk at all Collector´s hotels, but primarily at\nVictory. During these few months, I worked an average of 240 hours per month (days and\nnights).", "experiences/14/jobEndedOn": "9-2011", "experiences/14/jobLocation": "Stockholm/Sweden", "experiences/14/jobStartedOn": "5-2011", "experiences/14/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/14/title": "Various roles, manly front desk", "experiences/15/companyName": "SIAM CUSTOMER CONNECT SERVICE (Siam CCS),", "experiences/15/jobDescription": "Siam CCS is a Swedish call center which primarily sells products and services to consumers\n(B2C) in Sweden. The call center has existed since 2008 and then in November 2011 sold to\nCom 7 that drives the business forward under a new name.. The company has fifteen\nemployees, where of about ten are Swedish sellers.\nMy position at the company was to be team leader of the ten sellers. My tasks was to\nmotivate, engage and set clear sales target.", "experiences/15/jobEndedOn": "12-2009", "experiences/15/jobLocation": "Bangkok/Thailand", "experiences/15/jobStartedOn": "3-2009", "experiences/15/jobStillWorking": "false", "experiences/15/title": "Team leader/ Sales manager", "experiences/16/companyName": "LIDL SWEDEN KB,", "experiences/16/jobDescription": "Lidl is a German supermarket chain with a focus on discount stores. The company has\noperations in many parts of Europe. In 2003 the company began establishing stores in\nSweden. Lidl Sweden KB currently has over 140 stores and annual sales of 22 billion SEK in\na year.\nI was in charge of the smooth running of the store and all matters relating to the staff within\nthe shop with particular reference to recruitment, induction, training, discipline and appraisals.\nTo ensure correct staffing levels were maintained at all time. My objectives were to meet the\nset targets and to manage a p